#. type: Title ##
#, no-wrap
msgid "Build and installation"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"We strongly recommand the use of __GNU tar__ because some file path lenght "
"are greater than 100 caracters. Some tar version will silently ignore those "
"files like for example on HP-UX."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "First, you need to extract the source and change the current directory."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    $> tar xfz FusionInventory-Agent-2.2.5.tar.gz\n"
"    $> cd FusionInventory-Agent-2.2.5\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"Executing Makefile.PL will ensure all the required dependencies are "
"available and prepare the build tree."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "    $> perl Makefile.PL\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"At this point, you will probably have some missing required modules. See "
"Dependencies section for installing them. Once this is done, run the same "
"command again:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "    $> perl Makefile.Pl\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"This time the execution should success and you can finish the installation.  "
"Here again we recommand GNU make (gmake):"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    make\n"
"    make install\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"If you don't want to use the default directory (/usr/local), you can use the "
"PREFIX parameter during the Makefile.PL step:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    perl Makefile.PL PREFIX=/opt/fusioninventory\n"
"    make\n"
"    make install\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#, no-wrap
msgid "Tests"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"FusionInventory components come with a test-suite. You can run it after the "
"`perl Makefile.PL` with this command:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "    $> make test\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "The test-suites require some additional dependencies like Test::More."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#, no-wrap
msgid "Depedencies"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#, no-wrap
msgid "Perl dependencies"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"The easiest way to install perl dependencies is to use [cpanm](http://"
"cpanmin.us). Just run:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "    $> cpanm .\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"You can use the _--notest_ flag if you are brave and want to skip the test-"
"suite execution."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#, no-wrap
msgid "Offline installation of Perl dependencies"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"[[!template id=info text=\"You will need [cpanm](http://cpanmin.us).  See "
"above how to install it.\"]]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "First grab the tarball from the website and extract it."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    $> tar xfz FusionInventory-Agent-2.3.0.tar.gz\n"
"    $> cd FusionInventory-Agent-2.3.0\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"We use cpanm to fetch and extract the dependencies in the extlib directory."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "    $> cpanm --pureperl --installdeps -L extlib --notest .\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"This command should fail (2013-08-11) with an error regarding Params::"
"Validate. Just runs this last command:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "    $> cpanm --installdeps -L extlib --notest .\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"Now you can copy the directory to another machine and run the agent this way:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "    $> perl -Iextlib/lib/perl5 -Ilib fusioninventory-agent\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#, no-wrap
msgid "Other dependencies"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"On Solaris/SPARC, you must install sneep and record the Serial Number with "
"it.  Download it from <http://www.sun.com/download/products.xml?id=4304155a>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"On Windows, we use an additional dmidecode binary shipped in the windows "
"distribution to retrieve many informations not available otherwise, "
"including fine-grained multi-cores CPUs identification. Unfortunatly, this "
"binary is not reliable enough to be used on Windows 2003, leading to less "
"precise inventories."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"On Linux, lspci will be used to collect PCI, AGP, PCI-X, ... informations."
msgstr ""
